1545
01:32:03,836 --> 01:32:07,271
They blew up a planet! Fantastic!
We can do that! How did they do it?

1546
01:32:07,273 --> 01:32:09,873
What's the trick?
How did they do it?

1547
01:32:09,875 --> 01:32:11,875
Come on!
Help me!

1548
01:32:11,877 --> 01:32:14,044
"Has your association
with the institute...

1549
01:32:14,046 --> 01:32:16,780
Benefitted your life
in any way?"

1550
01:32:16,782 --> 01:32:19,216
I'd like to think about that a little.

1551
01:32:19,218 --> 01:32:21,218
What's the second biggest film?

1552
01:32:21,220 --> 01:32:24,755
<i>Jaws. All right,</i> jaws.
This is a good idea.

1553
01:32:24,757 --> 01:32:27,291
This is a good idea!
I can save this picture!

1554
01:32:27,293 --> 01:32:30,060
<i>Jaws.
My god, Pete.</i>

1555
01:32:30,062 --> 01:32:33,998
There is a gigantic fish down at the zoo. I
remember when we were down there filming.

1556
01:32:34,000 --> 01:32:37,468
The zookeeper's a fan of mine 'cause I gave
him an autograph. He'll let us in tonight.

1557
01:32:37,470 --> 01:32:39,937
I can get the family down there
in the middle of the night.

1558
01:32:39,939 --> 01:32:43,040
We'll have this confrontation...
Gigantic fish, family.

1559
01:32:43,042 --> 01:32:45,242
They'll meet.
I'll put music behind it.

1560
01:32:48,314 --> 01:32:50,814
I'm mentally ill.
I'm goin' nuts.

1561
01:32:50,816 --> 01:32:54,151
<i>God.</i> what am I <i>gonna do?</i>

1562
01:32:55,755 --> 01:32:58,088
What's the third biggest film?
<i>Gone with the wind.</i>

1563
01:32:58,090 --> 01:33:00,157
Timeless, timeless film. Beautiful film.

1564
01:33:02,194 --> 01:33:04,395
How did it end?
I didn't see it.

1565
01:33:04,397 --> 01:33:07,498
You didn't see it? You didn't
see <i>gone with the wind?</i>

1566
01:33:07,500 --> 01:33:11,135
Only the biggest film ever made.
You didn't see it?

1567
01:33:11,137 --> 01:33:14,405
My god, it was spectacular, Pete.
You oughta go see it.

1568
01:33:14,407 --> 01:33:17,674
You're in this business. They only
burn down the city of Atlanta.

1569
01:33:17,676 --> 01:33:20,644
A gigantic fire.
I mean...

1570
01:33:25,184 --> 01:33:27,718
I mean...

1571
01:33:29,855 --> 01:33:32,723
Mr. Brooks?

1572
01:33:34,760 --> 01:33:37,694
Mr. Brooks?

1573
01:33:43,803 --> 01:33:47,471
"Had you heard of the institute
before the project began?"

1574
01:33:47,473 --> 01:33:49,273
No.

1575
01:33:49,275 --> 01:33:52,810
"Which of the tests
did you enjoy the most?"

1576
01:33:56,348 --> 01:33:58,615
I enjoyed working with the computers.

1577
01:33:58,617 --> 01:34:03,320
I wouldn't say that I
<i>enjoyed any of the testing.</i>

1578
01:34:07,726 --> 01:34:10,027
Is it the coffee burning?

1579
01:34:10,029 --> 01:34:12,029
No, that smells a little like toast.

1580
01:34:12,031 --> 01:34:14,565
You didn't put anything...

1581
01:34:14,567 --> 01:34:17,034
Excuse me for a second, please.

1582
01:34:20,739 --> 01:34:23,006
Albert, what...
Trust me!

1583
01:34:23,008 --> 01:34:26,009
<i>Albert! Albert, my god!</i>

1584
01:34:26,011 --> 01:34:27,845
What are you doing?

1585
01:34:27,847 --> 01:34:31,482
What are you doing? Isn't it beautiful?
Look at that!

1586
01:34:31,484 --> 01:34:34,618
<i>The kids! Yeah, the kids! Save the kids!</i>

1587
01:34:34,620 --> 01:34:37,921
What a beautiful family!
This family is so beautiful!

1588
01:34:37,923 --> 01:34:39,957
Albert, stop! Are you crazy? Crazy?

1589
01:34:39,959 --> 01:34:43,894
Get out! Go ahead, get outta here!
Was David o. Selznick crazy?

1590
01:34:43,896 --> 01:34:46,196
Albert!
My god!

1591
01:34:46,198 --> 01:34:48,799
My god, Pete!
Pete!

1592
01:34:48,801 --> 01:34:52,536
My god!
Come here!

1593
01:34:52,538 --> 01:34:54,838
Are you okay?
Look!

1594
01:34:54,840 --> 01:34:56,640
Can you see it?
Can you see it?

1595
01:34:56,642 --> 01:34:59,143
Isn't it beautiful?
Focus for me, baby!

1596
01:34:59,145 --> 01:35:03,113
<i>I can't see!</i> It's beautiful!
<i>It's so beautiful!</i>

1597
01:35:03,115 --> 01:35:05,482
I can't see! It's beautiful!

1598
01:35:05,484 --> 01:35:08,152
- God, it's beautiful!
- Darling, run!

1599
01:35:08,154 --> 01:35:10,220
Albert, for god's sake, get out!

1600
01:35:10,222 --> 01:35:12,890
Save them! Save them!
Look at 'em go!

1601
01:35:12,892 --> 01:35:17,394
This is so exciting! This is a million
times better than a big fish!

1602
01:35:17,396 --> 01:35:21,064
This is so beautiful!
We did it, Pete!

1603
01:35:21,066 --> 01:35:23,634
We did it! We did it! I can't see!

1604
01:35:23,636 --> 01:35:26,003
<i>I can't</i> see! <i>We did it!</i>

1605
01:35:26,005 --> 01:35:28,472
Look at it, babe!

1606
01:35:28,474 --> 01:35:33,010
It's the most spectacular ending
anybody could've ever had!

1607
01:35:33,012 --> 01:35:36,847
Humor! Pathos!
Tragedy!

1608
01:35:36,849 --> 01:35:39,850
And it's real!
It's real!

1609
01:35:39,852 --> 01:35:43,554
Their house is really burning!

